The paper is about developing an efficient and flexible intrusion detection system using deep learning techniques, specifically a one-dimensional Convolutional Neural Network (1D-CNN). This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the focus is on detecting and preventing network attacks. The use of deep learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves supervised learning on time-series data, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks for detecting objects in images (cs.CV) is mentioned as a related technique.
